Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of natural language processing for content analysis of mathematical texts, which falls under the intersection of computer science and mathematics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DL (Deep Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these fields also involve techniques and methods related to natural language processing and content analysis.
